  "title" : "Update List of entities in one query jpa",
  "body" : "<p>I need to update a list of objects in one query.\nI have class Parent which has a list of Child in ManyToMany relation.\nI need to update a list of Parent by setting children list to empty(remove all children references from join table).\nCurrently i'm setting children list to empty and updating each entity in a query with a merge action,but when i have a large list of pharmacies there are too many queries.</p>\n\n<p>i tried this query: </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p><code>update Parent p set p.children=:children where p in (:parents)</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>where :children is a <code>new HashSet&lt;Child&gt;</code></p>\n\n<p>but it gives me error </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>unexpected end of subtree</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Is there any way to update a list in one query ? I'm using jpa entity manager.\nThanks.</p>\n"
}